# Card-audit puzzle (mtg-948 Part B) backing CLOSED issue mtg-510
# (Card Compatibility: Hypnotic Specter).
#
# Aspects exercised:
#   1. K:Flying — the 2/2 flier P1 cannot block (P1 has only a ground
#      Grizzly Bears), so its combat damage connects.
#   2. T:Mode$ DamageDone | ValidTarget$ Opponent | Execute$ TrigDiscard —
#      whenever Hypnotic Specter deals damage to an opponent, that player
#      discards a card at random (CR 603.2 damage trigger). P1 holds two
#      cards, so the discard is observable as a hand-size drop.
#
# HOW TO RUN / VERIFY interactively:
#   mtg tui --start-state test_puzzles/audit_hypnotic_specter_discard.pzl \
#       --p1 heuristic --p2 heuristic --seed 42 -v 2 --no-color-logs
# The log shows the flier connecting and "Trigger: Hypnotic Specter ...
# discards a card at random", with P1's hand shrinking.

[metadata]
Name:Hypnotic Specter flying + discard-on-damage trigger (audit mtg-510)
Goal:Win
Turns:5
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 attacks with a 2/2 flying Hypnotic Specter. P1's only creature is a ground Grizzly Bears that cannot block the flier (CR 702.9), so the Specter connects and its "deals damage to an opponent -> that player discards at random" trigger fires (CR 603.2). P1 holds two cards. Assertions confirm the trigger fired, P1 took damage, and P1's hand shrank from the discard.

[state]
turn=2
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=
p0library=Swamp; Swamp; Swamp; Swamp; Swamp
p0graveyard=
p0battlefield=Hypnotic Specter; Swamp; Swamp; Swamp
p0exile=

p1life=12
p1hand=Forest; Grizzly Bears
p1library=Forest; Forest; Forest; Forest; Forest
p1graveyard=
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears; Forest
p1exile=

[assertions]
# P1 took flying combat damage (the Specter connects past the ground blocker).
opponent life lt 12
# The discard-on-combat-damage trigger fires: each connection forces P1 to
# discard a card at random, which lands in P1's graveyard. P1 began with no
# graveyard, so a non-empty graveyard is the OBSERVABLE proof the discard
# trigger fired. (We assert the discard's effect, not a `trigger fired from
# Hypnotic Specter` event, because the event log only emits
# LogEvent::TriggerFired for death/leaves-battlefield watcher triggers today,
# NOT for DamageDone triggers — see the trigger-event instrumentation gap
# bug mtg-955.)
opponent graveyard count ge 1
